FBIS3-55636 "drsov007_m_94002" FBIS-SOV-94-007 Document Type:Daily Report 11 Jan 1994 CENTRAL ASIA Tajikistan Russian Troops Come Under Attack on Afghan Border Opposition Forces Attack Russian Troops LD1001232894 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1930 GMT 10 Jan 94 LD1001232894 Moscow Mayak Radio Network Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Text] The situation on the Tajik-Afghan border is not calm. According to officers of the Russian operational group in Dushanbe, over the past few days the Tajik opposition has continued its armed provocations from the territory of Afghanistan. The 12th and 13th outposts of the Russian border troops and the positions of the servicemen of the Russian 201st Motorized Rifle Division are being subjected to sporadic firing. Fortunately there are no casualties among the servicemen of the Russian Federation. According to the Russian military, the new spiral of tension on the border has been caused by the exacerbation of the military and political situation in Afghanistan, where clashes between various conflicting groups are taking place.
